<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p>In the imaginary external potential 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm28">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi>i</mi>
     <mo>⋅</mo>
     <mi>ω</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
     <mover accent="true">
      <mi>r</mi>
      <mo stretchy="false">→</mo>
     </mover>
     <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>, 
 <italic>q</italic> satisfies a modified diffusion equation as:
 <disp-formula id="FD3-polymers-11-01081">
  <label>(3)</label>
  <math id="mm29">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mfrac>
      <mn>1</mn>
      <mi>N</mi>
     </mfrac>
     <mfrac>
      <mrow>
       <mo>∂</mo>
       <mi>q</mi>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <mo>∂</mo>
       <mi>s</mi>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mfrac>
      <mrow>
       <msup>
        <mi>σ</mi>
        <mn>2</mn>
       </msup>
      </mrow>
      <mn>6</mn>
     </mfrac>
     <msup>
      <mo>∇</mo>
      <mn>2</mn>
     </msup>
     <mi>q</mi>
     <mo>−</mo>
     <mi>i</mi>
     <mo>⋅</mo>
     <mi>ω</mi>
     <mo>⋅</mo>
     <mi>q</mi>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> along with 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm30">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mi>q</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
     <mover accent="true">
      <mi>r</mi>
      <mo stretchy="false">→</mo>
     </mover>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <mn>0</mn>
     <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mn>1</mn>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>. In Equation (3), 
 <italic>ω</italic> takes 
 <italic>ω</italic>
 <italic>
  <sub>A</sub>
 </italic>, 
 <italic>ω
  <sub>B</sub>
 </italic>, and 
 <italic>ω</italic>
 <italic>
  <sub>C</sub>
 </italic> in turn as the contour variable 
 <italic>s</italic> passes through A, B, and then C blocks. It needs to be recalled that there is another function 
 <italic>q</italic>
 <sup>+</sup> conjugate to 
 <italic>q</italic>, so that 
 <italic>q</italic>
 <sup>+</sup> starts reversely from the other chain end with 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm31">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msup>
      <mi>q</mi>
      <mo>+</mo>
     </msup>
     <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
     <mover accent="true">
      <mi>r</mi>
      <mo stretchy="false">→</mo>
     </mover>
     <mo>,</mo>
     <mn>1</mn>
     <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
     <mo>=</mo>
     <mn>1</mn>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>. 
</p>
